<L>__{exterior parsonage back yard next day}
<A>__{reverend sullivan is up a ladder. cleaning a gutter. landon stands below, a few feet away, gathering his nerve. he walks over.}
<B>__{on ladder}
<A>__{the reverend is busy ignoring landon standing below. a long beat, then:}
<C>__{landon}
<P>__{(calling up)}
<D>__{sir. being ignored is beginning to feel preferable to being noticed.}
<A>__{the reverend looks down.}
<C>__{landon}
<D>__{i will be honest. i don't know if i can pray, but i can do just about anything else.}
<A>__{neither landon nor the reverend see jamie come out of the house and walk over.}
<B>__{on ground}
<A>__{landon shields his eyes with a hand to see the reverend better.}
<C>__{landon}
<D>__{whatever you need. whatever jamie needs. i'm here.}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{i could start by driving her to school }
<C>__{jamie}
<D>__{i'm not going back to school.}
<A>__{landon and her father both turn to her. pale, wane. they understand what she is saying.}
<C>__{jamie}
<D>__{you can tell anyone you want. i don't care.}
<A>__{she goes into the house. landon and reverend sullivan look at each other, then away, uncomfortable. that didn't sound like her.}
